%N A173548 Number of 3 X 3 magilatin squares with positive values < n.
%C A173548 A magilatin squares has equal row and column sums and no number repeated in any row or column.
%C A173548 a(n) is given by a quasipolynomial of degree 5 and period 60.
%H A173548 T. Zaslavsky, <a href="/A173548/b173548.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 4..10000</a>.
%H A173548 Matthias Beck and Thomas Zaslavsky, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/math/0506315">An enumerative geometry for magic and magilatin labellings</a>, arXiv:math/0506315 [math.CO], 2005.
%H A173548 Matthias Beck and Thomas Zaslavsky, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s00026-006-0296-4">An enumerative geometry for magic and magilatin labellings</a>, Annals of Combinatorics, 10 (2006), no. 4, pages 395-413. MR 2007m:05010. Zbl 1116.05071.
%H A173548 Matthias Beck and Thomas Zaslavsky, <a href="https://cs.uwaterloo.ca/journals/JIS/VOL13/Zaslavsky/sls.html">Six little squares and how their numbers grow</a>, Journal of Integer Sequences, 13 (2010), Article 10.6.2.
%H A173548 <a href="/index/Rec#order_19">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (0,2,2,0,-3,-3,-2,1,4,4,1,-2,-3,-3,0,2,2,0,-1).
%F A173548 G.f.: x^2/(1-x)^2 * ( 12*x^2/(x-1)^2 - 36*x^3/(x-1)^3 - 72*x^3/((x-1)*(x^2-1)) - 36*x^3/(x^3-1) - 72*x^4/((x-1)^2*(x^2-1)) - 36*x^4/((x-1)*(x^3-1)) - 72*x^4/(x^2-1)^2 + 72*x^5/((x-1)^3*(x^2-1)) + 72*x^5/((x-1)^2*(x^3-1)) + 144*x^5/((x-1)*(x^2-1)^2) + 72*x^5/((x-1)*(x^4-1)) + 108*x^5/((x^2-1)*(x^3-1)) + 72*x^5/(x^5-1) + 144*x^6/((x-1)*(x^2-1)*(x^3-1)) + 72*x^6/(x^2-1)^3 + 144*x^6/((x^2-1)*(x^4-1)) + 72*x^6/(x^3-1)^2 + 72*x^7/((x^2-1)^2*(x^3-1)) + 72*x^7/((x^2-1)*(x^5-1)) + 72*x^7/((x^3-1)*(x^4-1)) + 72*x^8/((x^3-1)*(x^5-1)) ).
%F A173548 a(n) = (36*n^5 - 765*n^4 + 8080*n^3 - 45228*n^2 + 119280*n - 106848)/120 + (n mod 2)*(18*n^2-252*n+1269)/8 - ((2*n^2+2*n) mod 3)*(3*n-34)*8/3 - ((2*n^2+n+2) mod 5)*144/5 + 64/3*[(n mod 3)=2] - 72*[(n mod 4)=3]. - _Hoang Xuan Thanh_, Jul 14 2026
%t A173548 LinearRecurrence[{0, 2, 2, 0, -3, -3, -2, 1, 4, 4, 1, -2, -3, -3, 0, 2, 2, 0, -1}, {12, 48, 120, 384, 1068, 2472, 4896, 9072, 15516, 25608, 40296, 61608, 91068, 131640, 185136, 255960, 346860, 463248, 608088}, 31] (* _Jean-François Alcover_, Nov 05 2018 *)
